message: docs:Update documentation for the new changes

Updated README

- Fix: Removed image height constraint.
- Change: Removed Video Demo, wasn't working.
- Change: Clean-up.
Changed license and updated copyright info

Setting up for release

- Add/Change: Updated `setup.py`:
  - Set upper bounds for package dependencies to avoid breakage.
  - Updated classifiers and keywords.
- Change: Updated package installation step in github workflow.
- Change: Updated changelog.

Updated Requirements and Supported Terminals

- Add: Indicated partial support for Windows.
- Change: Updated list of supported terminal emulators.

Changed package name; Bumped package to v0.1.1

- Unable to upload to PyPI as `term-img` due to a "similar name" response.
- Bumped to 0.1.1 because 0.1.0 had been uploaded with the old package name (for a badge) in the README.

Renamed project, CLI executable, user directory

- Change: `term-img` -> `term-image`.

The name `term-img` clashes with that of a slightly similar project written in JavaScript.
The new name also tallies with the package name on PyPI.

[docs] Updated the package name in the docs

- Change: Updated the README.
- Change: Updated the docs.
- Change: Updated docstrings and comments.

Updated README

- Add: Added docs build status badge.
- Change: Updated WIP section.
Added Credits and Donation sections to the README
Updated the README and fixed a typo in the docs
[docs] Updated the README and planned features

[lib,docs] Removed all deprecated features

- Change: Removed all deprecated features.
- Add: Added a notice concerning the API status to the README and docs.

Now adhering to the Semantic Versioning specification for major version zero for the sake of rapid development.
